						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">No date</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, in three fragments engraved in characters of about the 16th century, seems to record a gift of land by purchase to provide for worship and food offerings to the god at night, by Tunakaṇḍi Siṅgama-nāyaka, grandson of Naragiri-nāyaka (cf. No. 642).</p>						

						</summary>
